                    state treasury during the past year: $3,338.89 in taxes on bank dividends;
                    $3,527.60 on corporation stocks; $30,760.06 on real and personal property;
                    $5,907.57 on half-mills; $25.86 on net earnings or income; $400.00 on enrollment
                    of laws; $333.08 on tonnage; $713.39 on writs; $9,402.58 on collateral
                    inheritance; $1,034.15 on tavern licenses; $4,217.18 on retailers' licenses;
                    $38.00 on billiard room licenses; $7.60 on peddlers' licenses; $266.00 on
                    restaurant licenses; $166.25 on distillery and brewery licenses. The total paid
                    by Franklin county was $59,138.15.</summary>
